main event: Radar painted one large target considered to be out of the ordinary due to its high altitude and sudden altitude changes at tremendous speed. The target disappeared from the scope due to scope limitations.
interesting points: The radar target was measured at an unusually high altitude of 74,000 feet, and in excess of 96,000 feet.
The target climbed out of the radar's scope limitations after being tracked for 5 minutes.
The radar used was a ground-based electronic system type AN/FPPSB.
The radar was operated by a SSGT with 11 years of radar experience and an A/2C witness.
The weather conditions at the time included scattered clouds, good visibility, and light winds.
